{"/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02/data/sn92073203/00332893014/1937120902/0615.xml":{"full_text":"THURSDAY, DECEMBER IM?\nUpturn In Business In \u20193B Is\nPredicted By Leading Bankers\nRoger Babson Also Thinks Pre\nsent Recession \u201cBlessing In\nDisguise.\u201d\nThe current slump in business\nthroughout the nation will not re\nsult in another depression the up\nturn will come in 1938, leading\nbankers in the country and Roger\nW. Babson declared last Sunday.\nThe concensus of opinion among\n125 bank presidents and executives\nof the most important banks in 44\nstates having a \u25a0total deposits of\ntwelve billion dollars, is that the\npresent business recession will run\nits course for four more months or\nmore, bhit the upturn will then\ncome.\nIn his regular forecast column\nSunday, Mr. Babson declared that\nin his opinion the present slump is\na \u201cblessing in disguise\u201d. He thinks\nthat the country is just passing\nthrough a re-adjustment period.\nLewis said the replies indicated\nbankers believe an upturn in busi\nness is dependent upon a demon\nstrated change in attitude on the\npart of the administration toward\nbusiness.\nRanking first among recovery\nmeasures suggested, Lewis said,\nwas repeat of the undistributed\nearnings tax; next balancing of the\nbudget; third, lowering of taxes on\ncapital gains; fourth, increase in\nrail freight rates to provide rea\nsonable return on investment, and\nfifth, encouragement to utilities to\npromote expansion.\nOBITUARY\nWiley Winfred Burkett, fcon (of\nMr. and Mrs. G. W. Burkett, was\nborn May 3rd, 1879, and on the\nmorning of Oct. 22nd, he was called\nto his reward, being 58 years, 6\nmonths and 18 days of age.\nHe was married to Miss Eunice\nLittle Aug. 15, 1903, and to this\nunion were born 5 children, 4 liv\ning, one having died at the age of\n6 years. The living are Glenn and\nWarner, of Widemouth, W. Va., and\nPearl and Stella of Jefferson. Al\nso surviving him are his wife, 2\nbrothers: Rev. Roby M. Burkett and\nMr. Tom Burkett; 2 sisters, Mrs.\nLaura Marsh and Mrs. Mary Marsh;\n2 grandchildren and with many rel\natives and friends.\nBrother Wiley professed faith in\nChrist as his personal saviour and\nunited with the Friendship Baptist\nChurch October 28th, 1895, where\nhe lived a loyal and consistant\nmember.\nHe was faithful in his Christian\nduties and in 1914 was ordained\nto the deaconship of his church\nwhere he\u2019 served faithfully and\nwell until he was forced to stop by\nsickness. About 8 years hgo he\nwas confined to his bed and this\ntime was unable to attend his\nchurch, but yet he trusted in the\nsaviour that had saved him, and\nwhen the end came he fell asleep\nin the arms of Jesus.\nPossibly no one can ever imag\nine the intense suffering that he\npassed through, having suffered\ncontinually for 8 years. 'V Yet he\nwas patient and never complained.\nHe will be missed by the church\nand community, but most of all by\nhis loving wife and children who\nhave so paitidritly and lovingly\ncared for him through the yeans of\nhis illness. Miss Ella Marsh, a niece\nof his, is to be highly commended\nfor her kind and faithful service to\nhim and the family in their dis\ntress.\nI Remember\nI YOUR C AR! I\naW\nWhen you threat your car to a\nChristmas present, everyone can rwr w\njg enjoy it. We have just what you W\nJ want. Yes, genuine Ford Acces- W\nf& series. gg\nFORD HOT AIR HEATERSSI4 50\n(Completely installed) w\nWe have a good selection of used cars and trucks, at spe-\n5 cial Christmas bargain prices. _Our stock includes: w\nI USED BARGAINS\n6 1930 Chevrolet Coach 1935 Ford Coupe g\nm 1929 Chevrolet Coach 1936 Ford Coach g\n1937 Chevrolet Coach 1933 Chevrolet Coach g\njgt 929 Chevrolet Coach 1933 Chevrolet Coupe g\nM 1934 Chevrolet Master Coupe g\n|t A SEE THE NEW 1938 FORDS! g\nB ASHE MOTOR CO. g\ng WSST JEFFERSON, N. C.\nPHOTO SAVED A LIFE\nr s A'\nS\nJ K S\nSHr HHMii\ni H 111 ill\nI\nA copy of the original photo sent\nto Gen. Francisco Franco by Mrs.\nHarold Dahl in a plea to the rebel\nleader for the life and freedom of\nher husband, Harold Dahl of Cham\nr paign, Hl., who was captured by in-\nsurgent forces while flying for the\nSpanish government in the civil\ns war. Impressed by the beauty of\nl the American girl, Franco spared\nL the life of her husband and prom?\nised he would be freed.\n\nHilarious Play\nTo Be Given At\nElkland Dec. 11\n\u201cA Ready-Made Family\u201d To Be\nPresented Again by Popular\nRequest.\nAt the request of the patrons of\nElkland high school the hilarious,\nf three-act comedy, \u201cA Ready Made\nFamily\u201d will be given again in the\nschool auditorium on Saturday\nnight, December 11, at 7:45.\nIn spite of the bitter cold of No\nvember 20, which prevented\nsome of the folks from attending,\nthe clever impersonations of the\nstudent actors made the first per\nformance of the play so successful\nthat those who were there de-\nI clared they would go through a\nblizzard to see it again. Everyone\nhopes for better weather this time,\nbut if a little rain or snow should\nblow up, don\u2019t let them keep you\nfrom seeing \u201cA Ready Made Fami\nly.\u201d\nThe usual admission \u2014fifteen and\ntwenty-five cents\u2014will be charged,\nand the proceeds will go toward i\nbuying equipment and library\nbooks for the school.\nVAUGHT-SAWYER\nMr. and Mrs. John Vaught, of\nCrumpler announce the marriage\nof their daughter, Peggy Pauline, to\nJess R. Sawyer, of Loyland ,West\nVirginia, on Monday, Nov. 29.\nThe popular couple were united\nin marriage by Rev. R. H. Stone, at\nhis home in Jefferson.\nSo as it has pleased the Lord to\ncall him in death, let us be submis\nsive to His will and be ready when\ni the call of death comes for us, that\nwe may meet Him where no part\ning ever comes.\nWritten by\nREV. W. E. DENNEY.\nTHE SKYLANL POST, WEST JEFFERSON, N. Q\nr 7 I\nCAR\u00bb\nSHS JMt\nWf\u00dff ARE 5 time; AS MANY f J 'E$ IN TriS 16/2 STATE lEGffIAWRE THERE IVERf\nIN. N.C AS